Task 1: Configure Local AAA Authentication for Console Access on R1

Objective: Use the local database for console login authentication.

Configuration Commands
R1> enable
R1# configure terminal

R1(config)# username Admin1 secret admin1pa55
R1(config)# aaa new-model
R1(config)# aaa authentication login default local

R1(config)# line console 0
R1(config-line)# login authentication default
R1(config-line)# exit

R1(config)# end
R1# exit
Login Credentials
Username: Admin1
Password: admin1pa55
Task 2: Configure Local AAA Authentication for VTY (Telnet) Lines on R1

Objective: Use local database authentication for Telnet access.

Configuration Commands
R1# configure terminal

R1(config)# aaa authentication login TELNET-LOGIN local

R1(config)# line vty 0 4
R1(config-line)# login authentication TELNET-LOGIN
R1(config-line)# exit

R1(config)# banner motd # *****AUTHORIZED ACCESS ONLY***** #

R1(config)# end
Task 3: Configure Server-Based AAA Authentication using TACACS+ on R2

Objective: Authenticate users using a TACACS+ server.

Configuration Commands
R2> enable
R2# configure terminal

R2(config)# username Admin2 secret admin2pa55

R2(config)# tacacs-server host 192.168.2.2
R2(config)# tacacs-server key tacacspa55

R2(config)# aaa new-model
R2(config)# aaa authentication login default group tacacs+ local

R2(config)# line console 0
R2(config-line)# login authentication default
R2(config-line)# exit

R2(config)# end
R2# exit
Login Credentials
Username: Admin2
Password: admin2pa55
